"v.使高兴，使满足 【英】 v. 使高兴，使满足(to give pleasure or satisfaction) 【考】 gratify : desire / slake : thirsty(使满足消除欲望/解 渴消除口渴)反义词: aggrieve(使苦恼); irk(使苦恼) 【记】 grat(高兴)+ify→使 高兴 【同】 同根词：gratulant( 表示高兴的); gratitude(感激之情) 【例】 Anne was gratified by his efforts to help her. v. 使高兴, 使满足 = satisfy 【记】grat高兴 【参】gratulant(adj 表示满足的); gratitude(n 感激之情); 【类】gratify: desire = slake: thirsty 使满足消除欲望 = 解渴消除口渴 【反】aggrieve(v 使苦恼); irk(v 使苦恼); displease(v 使不快) 【记】满足了，他很高兴，表示感谢grateful；great 让他连说great 太好了 gratify (v.)  c.1400, ""to bestow grace upon;"" 1530s, ""to show gratitude to,"" from French gratifier (16c.) or directly from Latin gratificari ""to do favor to, oblige, gratify,"" from gratus ""pleasing"" (see grace (n.)) + root of facere ""make, do, perform"" (see factitious). Meaning ""to give pleasure to"" is from 1560s. Related: Gratified; gratifying."
